        'description' => 'Confusion about the new tax slabs? We explain the difference between Old and New Regime and help you choose the right one.',
        'category' => 'Blog',
        'type' => 'post',
        'content' => '<h2>New vs Old Tax Regime (FY 2024-25): The Final Verdict</h2>
<p>The New Regime (Default)</p>
<p>The Old Regime</p>
<p>Breakeven Point</p>
<p>Check Your Tax</p>
<p>Budget 2024 made the New Regime the default tax option. But is it actually better for you? The answer depends on your investments.</p>
<p>Compare both regimes instantly.</p>
<p>Philosophy: Lower tax rates, zero paperwork.</p>
<p>Philosophy: Incentivize savings and investments.</p>
<p>Generally, if your total deductions (HRA + 80C + 80D) exceed ₹3.75 Lakhs, the Old Regime might save you more tax. Otherwise, the New Regime is usually better and simpler.</p>
<p>Pros: No need to invest in insurance or PPF just to save tax. Higher Standard Deduction (₹75,000). Tax-free up to ₹7 Lakhs.</p>
<p>Cons: You lose HRA, LTA, and Section 80C deductions.</p>
<p>Pros: You can claim HRA (Rent), Home Loan Interest (up to 2L), and 80C (1.5L).</p>
<p>Cons: Higher tax slab rates. Complex paperwork.</p>',
